meaning: fill in, fill up, make good

onyomiExamples.meaning: filling (up), replenishing, filling in (tooth), loading (gun with ammunition, camera with film, etc.), packing, plugging

kunyomiExamples.meaning: to insert, to put in (such that there is a snug fit), to button, to put on (something that envelops, e.g. gloves, ring), to have sex, to fuck, to pigeonhole (into a particular category), to place a ring-shaped object around something (esp. one that restricts freedom, such as handcuffs), to entrap, to set someone up (e.g. frame them for a crime, etc.)
